====Noun====
{{en-noun|-|s}}

# {{lb|en|uncountable}} Action given to provide [[assistance]]; [[aid]].
#: {{ux|en|I need some '''help''' with my homework.}}
# {{lb|en|usually|uncountable}} Something or someone which provides assistance with a task.
#: {{ux|en|He was a great '''help''' to me when I was moving house.}}
#: {{ux|en|I've printed out a list of math '''helps'''.}}
# [[documentation|Documentation]] provided with [[computer]] [[software]], etc. and accessed using the computer.
#: {{ux|en|I can't find anything in the '''help''' about rotating an image.}}
# {{lb|en|usually|uncountable}} One or more people employed to help in the maintenance of a house or the operation of a farm or enterprise.
#: {{ux|en|The '''help''' is coming round this morning to clean.}}
#: {{ux|en|Most of the hired '''help''' is seasonal, for the harvest.}}
# {{lb|en|uncountable}} Correction of deficits, as by psychological counseling or medication or social support or remedial training.
#: {{ux|en|His suicide attempts were a cry for '''help'''.}}
#: {{ux|en|He really needs '''help''' in handling customer complaints.}}
#: {{ux|en|“He’s a real road-rager.” / “Yup, he really needs '''help''', maybe anger management.”}}

=====Usage notes=====
* The sense “people employed to help in the maintenance of a house” is usually an uncountable [[mass noun]]. A countable form - “a hired help”, “two hired helps” - is attested, but now less common. ''[[helper|Helper]]'' could be used if no more specific noun is available.

